<br>
  In order to understand something we might have done wrong, one must retrospect upon the event.  This retrospection often involves more thought than feeling.  But it gives us the ability to weigh all the possibilities and options in hind-sight.  This makes it easy to rationalize the event and not account for how it made you and other existing members feel.  <br>
 <br>
  However, the experiences accounted for in retrospect can be used to create a more clear strategy of what To do or Not to do next time.  If one ignores the oppourtunity to take advantage of retrospection, then one will likely arrive in the same situation again.  I guess this is probably a 'sin'.  But I don't believe its possible to survive physically and have time to retrospect all of our 'possible' wrongdoings without damaging another aspect of our humanity in the process.  <br>
<br>
  I'm sure you have probably hurt someone unintentionally as we all have.  Mabye you still haven't realized it.  (We all think about our school days and feel bad sometimes)   Whether you were the offensive socialite or the defensive non-conformer, we have all thrown a wrench into someone's 'way' of life.  But, if someone kills someone and then begs God for forgiveness then he is basically asking God not to teach him a lesson by way of Truth.  IMO, Jesus died for our sins, (I agree with Lukaria when she said that we don't have to)  Thnx for bringing that up Lukaria <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   So if the murderer kills someone then he must feel the reflection of the Waves he has created.  Of course that depends upon the act as well.  In self-defense, what the hell are you suppossed to do otherwise?  <br>
<br>
  People's view of Truth is kinda distorted.  Its not just a fact, its the value of an event that always creates balance in life.  If I am Manson and kill someone, then I am acting out some type of protest.  This protest is a result of 'bad' feelings.   These bad feelings came about through a life (probably) full of a lack of love and of truth.  Charles emmulated the fuked up system that he lived in, focused his energy on hate rather than sadness and shared his record of events with others in a way that he felt was equivocal.   Thank God we are not God.  <br>
 <br>
  So, I don't see a Christians having to 'beg' for forgiveness.  But if you want God to 'go easy' on th truth(Or discipline) then you could ask him to do so.  Mabye this is what people are actually doing.   Of course you can't expect everyone to have some kind of metaphysical belief at their fingertips.   A story of some sort, but I sure am not one of the mechanical types who have such a strong foundtion of mechanical knowledge that they could solve many mechanically based probelms 10 times faster than I.  Everyone is different.  <br>
<br>
  However, I do know that there can be requests made of God.  Not saying he will always act upon them.  But, I am saying that feelings, Or this kneeling and praying thing, can make a REAL difference for one's life.  As you know I have very limited knowledge of the Bible but I do remember that Jesus said, &quot;with faith the size of a mustard seed, one can move a mountain&quot;.   Something like that.  I know that God works through physical means when necassary.  In my experience(not making claims for other people here)  I have found that communication with God can make 'things' happen.  Yes, even physical events.  There is a correlation between physical nature and the abstract.  I don't know exactly how but for some reason, establishing a clear communication line by way of love and truth can make this change.  Actually meditating is a great way to establish a clear line of communication.  There has to be a clear bond between one's feelings and there thoughts.  There are many things I have learned simply because I asked God for the Knowledge to know or understand or whatever.   I would rather not share the all of the knowledge and none of the events as it is very special to me and do not want to 'put' it out there for critiscism.  I try to keep the very special things between me, God and loved ones.    Crap we are closing, gotta go.  <br>
